{{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Tort Law | cover = | editor = John Goldberg, [[Jules Coleman]] | discipline = [[Tort|Tort law]] | abbreviation = J. Tort Law | bluebook = J. Tort L. | publisher = [[Berkeley Electronic Press]] | country = United States | frequency = Biannually | history = 2006-present | openaccess = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.bepress.com/jtl/ | ISSN = 1932-9148 }} The '''''Journal of Tort Law''''' is a [[peer review]]ed [[law review]] covering [[tort|tort law]]. It was established in 2006 and is published by the [[Berkeley Electronic Press]]. The [[editor-in-chief|editors-in-chief]] are John Goldberg and [[Jules Coleman]]. The journal is indexed in [[Index to Foreign Legal Periodicals]], [[Intute]], [[Scopus]], and [[Westlaw]]. According to the Washington and Lee Law Journal Ranking, the ''Journal of Tort Law'' has the highest impact factor among 7 journals specializing in tort law and was overall ranked 64th among 1087 law journals in 2010.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://lawlib.wlu.edu/LJ/ | title=Washington and Lee Law Journal Ranking | publisher=[[Washington and Lee University School of Law]] | accessdate=October 20, 2011}}</ref>
