{{Infobox university | name = West Ukrainian University of Economics and Law | native_name = Західноукраїнський економіко-правничий університет | image = Frankiwsk Melnychuka 14 DSC 5025 26-101-0273.JPG | latin_name = | motto = | mottoeng = | established = 1991 | type = | staff = | rector = Yaroslav Gryta | departments = | students = 2 000 | city = [[Ivano-Frankivsk]] | country = [[Ukraine]] | campus = | affiliations = | website = |}}
'''West Ukrainian University of Economics and Law''' is a Ukrainian University in [[Ivano-Frankivsk]].
==History== The university started its activities in [[Bukovyna]] in 1991 as a Ukrainian Free Institute of Management and Business (UVIMB). From 1995 as Czernowitz School of Economics and Law (Economics and Law Institute in [[Chernivtsi]] ).
The university was re-registered in 2003 on the basis Ivano-Frankivsk Faculty of Law and Business Economics, which was acted as a structural unit of Czernowitz School of Economics and Law from 1992. It is now Czernowitz School of Economics and Law is detached structural divisions of the university.
